{"id":"5771","name":"happy-hour-letter-of-the-law","title":"Happy Hour: Letter Of The Law","author":"Christy Frink","date":"2010-09-22T19:00:00-05:00","tags":[],"categories":["News"],"contentEncoded":"<div id=\"greet_block\"><noscript><div class=\"greet_block wpgb_cornered\"><div class=\"greet_text\"><div class=\"greet_image\"><a href=\"http://nashvillest.com/feed/rss/\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"http://nashvillest.com/wp-content/plugins/wp-greet-box/images/rss_icon.png\" alt=\"WP Greet Box icon\"></a></div>Hello there! If you are new here, you might want to <a href=\"http://nashvillest.com/feed/rss/\" rel=\"nofollow\"><strong>subscribe to the RSS feed</strong></a> for updates on this topic.<div style=\"clear:both\"></div><div class=\"greet_block_powered_by\">Powered by <a href=\"http://omninoggin.com/projects/wordpress-plugins/wp-greet-box-wordpress-plugin/\" title=\"WP Greet Box WordPress Plugin\" style=\"text-decoration:none;\">WP Greet Box</a> <a href=\"http://omninoggin.com/\" title=\"WordPress Plugin\" style=\"text-decoration:none;\">WordPress Plugin</a></div><div style=\"clear:both\"></div></div></div></noscript></div><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/opishposh/5006741718/in/pool-715021@N24/\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.flickr.com&apos;]);\"><img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"http://farm5.static.flickr.com/4085/5006741718_b756fafd38.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"333\" height=\"500\"></a></p><ul><li>The Sommet Group, who lost their naming rights for the downtown arena to Bridgestone a few months back, seems to be continuing on a downward spiral. While being investigated for all kinds of tax-related shadiness, their CEO and his wife were found to be in contempt of court for misplacing documents and computers that are pertinent to the investigation. [<a href=\"http://www.wsmv.com/news/25116556/detail.html\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.wsmv.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">WSMV</a>]</li><li>We always love to see our favorite hangouts get some national attention, which is probably why we were so excited to see The Patterson House in GQ&#x2019;s list of the 25 Best Cocktail Bars in America. [<a href=\"http://www.wkrn.com/Global/story.asp?S=13200322\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.wkrn.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">WKRN</a>]</li><li>In case you&#x2019;re playing along at home, the Music City Center is 10% complete. [<a href=\"http://www.wsmv.com/news/25120102/detail.html\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.wsmv.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">WSMV</a>]</li><li>The Preds penned a new deal with 102.9 FM The Buzz, making it their official flagship station that will broadcast all their games. Speaking of the Preds, the preseason kicks off tomorrow and if you see some green spandex, we certainly had nothing to do with it. [<a href=\"http://nashvillecitypaper.com/content/sports/predators-announce-new-flagship-radio-broadcasts?utm_source=feedburner&amp;utm_medium=feed&amp;utm_campaign=Feed%3A+NashvilleCityPaper-LatestNews+%28Nashville+City+Paper+-+Latest+News%29&amp;utm_content=Google+Reader\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;nashvillecitypaper.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">City Paper</a>]</li></ul><p style=\"text-align: left;\"><em>Photo by </em><a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/opishposh/5006741718/in/pool-715021@N24/\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.flickr.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\"><em>O Pish Posh</em></a><em>.</em></p><p>Related posts:<ol><li><a href=\"http://nashvillest.com/2008/07/07/happy-hour-by-the-letter-of-the-law/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Permanent Link: Happy Hour: By The Letter Of The Law\">Happy Hour: By The Letter Of The Law</a></li></ol></p>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<!--END .entry-content .article-->"}